**Michael Bayer ([@zzzeek](https://github.com/zzzeek)) wrote:**

you dont need a monkeypatch if you're on 0.9.  Use the [handle_error](http://docs.sqlalchemy.org/en/rel_0_9/core/events.html#sqlalchemy.events.ConnectionEvents.handle_error) event:


```
@event.listens_for(Engine, "handle_error")
def handle_exception(context):
    if isinstance(context.original_exception,
        psycopg2.OperationalError) and \
        "SSL disconnect" in str(context.original_exception):
        context.is_disconnect=True

```
